genresAdvancedInfo.name: marathi traditional
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Marathi traditional music is a genre of music that has been passed down through generations in the Indian state of Maharashtra. It encompasses a wide range of styles, including bhajans, abhangs, lavanis, and powadas. Traditional Marathi music is often performed on traditional instruments such as the dholki, harmonium, and tabla, and features lyrics that touch on themes of devotion, spirituality, and social justice.
